<paragraph id="8B947A5ECB34C205CEA7F8AEFF54C6A3" blockId="40.[151,1437,821,1967]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B95FA64CCB34C205CEA7F8AEFEC2C67A" box="[198,330,1861,1886]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Greek 
<emphasis id="B95FA64CCB34C205CC78F8AEFDD2C67A" box="[537,602,1861,1886]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">chion</emphasis>
“snow” and 
<emphasis id="B95FA64CCB34C205CD60F8AEFCB0C67A" box="[769,824,1861,1886]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">thrix</emphasis>
“hair,” in reference to the white setae of the metasoma.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B947A5ECB34C205CEA7F87EFCC2C68B" blockId="40.[151,1437,821,1967]" box="[198,842,1941,1967]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
